modules.description: This module handles the rewriting of internationalization (i18n) constructs during OCaml compilation. It transforms expressions and extensions related to localization, using configurable module names and path manipulations. Key operations include constructing identifiers, applying arguments, and expanding expressions based on translation rules.

This module rewrites internationalization constructs during OCaml compilation, transforming expressions and extensions based on localization rules. It supports configurable module names and path manipulations, enabling identifier construction, argument application, and expression expansion. Developers can use it to automatically generate translation-aware code, such as rewriting `[%i18n "Hello"]` into a call to a specified translation function with contextual arguments. Specific examples include expanding localized strings into function calls with metadata or adapting translation keys based on file paths.
